Data Scientist- London UK		Brightstar Corp.		Miami, FL		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><strong>Job Description<br /></strong>This is an amazing opportunity for a talented Data Scientist who is keen on affecting real world problems. With a very collaborative group you will be able to learn and theorize quantitative techniques with other intelligent individuals to influence leadership in identifying opportunities for Brightstar and our clients to operate more efficiently, As a Data Scientist, you do more than just crunch the numbers. You work with Executive Leadership, Functional Business Leaders and Marketing teams to adjust Brightstar's practices. Identifying the problem is only half the job; you a vital part of the solution <br />As a Data Scientist, you will be responsible for early stage ideation and innovation for new marketing data offerings. You will do this by exploring existing statistical methods and designing new ways to harness meaningful insights from consumer data in the telecommunications services industry. As a Data Scientist in Brightstar, you will be "at the center of the wireless ecosystem," ™ leading the global market business intelligence to pioneer new ways in which to produce robust and innovative analytical solutions across the globe. <br />You will be joining an organization with relentless commitment to cutting edge quantitative techniques to maximize customer focused businesses and its profitable growth. You will need to bring an array of technical skills to the table as well as be able to influence decision making with senior stakeholders around the implementation of specialized applications and business analytics. You will need to be self-motivated and have a proven track record of strong problem solving skills in industrial settings and model building using data mining techniques. <br />Responsibilities <br />* Conceiving and communicating frameworks for approaching questions, and executing self-directed investigation and analysis <br />* Selecting and implementing methods to extract data from new sources <br />* Selecting and implementing technologies to store and process data from these new sources (structured and unstructured) <br />* Designing algorithms to convert client questions and datasets into insightful answers <br />* Creating robust visualizations that illustrate to clients the insight unlocked from their data <br />* Working with diverse data sources—time series, spatial, graph, semi-structured/unstructured—and build statistical/machine learning models to uncover and predict value-driven insights <br />* Engaging clients to understand the "what" that they want to see and to develop a strategy on "how" to get that from the data being used <br />* Establishing benchmarks and characterizing best practices <br />* Working with business teams to develop and commercialize products<br /><br /><strong>Preferred Educational Requirements<br /></strong>Advanced Degree<br /><br /><strong>Requirements/Skills<br /></strong>Key qualifications for Senior Data Scientist: <br />* Advanced Degree in Computer Science, Applied Math, Statistics, or a quantitative field <br />* 3+ years professional experience analyzing complex data sets, modeling, machine learning, and/or large-scale data mining <br />* Algorithms, Monte Carlo, Hadoop/Grid based programming <br />* SAS, R, Matlab, Mathematica, C++, Python <br />* 2+ years' experience with NoSQL databases and tools such as Hadoop, Hive, Cassandra, MongoDB, Redis, ElasticSearch, and HBase <br />* 2+ years' experience with data visualization tools such as Tableau, QlikView, OBIEE, Cognos, Business Objects, MicroStrategy, SAS BI <br />* Experience with Spark and MapReduce <br />* Programming experience in R, Java, Scala, Python (NumPy, SciPy, Pandas, Blaze, Bokeh) <br />* Expertise in SQL databases, queries, and stored procedures <br />* Graph databases such as Neo4J or OrientDB <br />* Superior ability to break down large, complex business problems into discrete, achievable steps <br />* Preparation of analytics results and presentation to managers and clients (both technical and non-technical) <br />* Self-directed investigations and managing own work under tight time constraints <br />* Proven ability to identify relationships within large, not obviously related data sets <br />* Ability to work with incomplete/imperfect data <br />* Excellent written and verbal communication skills<br /><br /><strong>About Brightstar<br /></strong>Imagine working with the largest and most-loved brands in wireless. Exciting? Yes. But even more, you'll be helping people across the globe gain more access to more mobile device technology-with a better user experience, and getting the most value out of their devices...for life.<br />Are you one of us?<br />Impressed by the power of mobile connectivity and energized by the shocking pace of its evolution, we're the innovators helping define and drive an entire industry of dynamic mobile-related services. We're inspired by technology, motivated to serve, and growing fast with tremendous opportunity.<br />Bring us your best<br />And because mobile never stops... neither do we. No matter what your job may be at Brightstar, we'll be counting on you - starting Day One - to push the envelope with your creative thinking, quick execution, and a driving desire to serve our customers along with dedicated co-workers. Bring us your best, and together we'll make the world more mobile!</div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"></div>